Easy dessert for great response from guests. We serve it with fresh whipped cream or french vanilla ice cream. Always a hit!

Rating: 4
I modified this recipe with left over Easter panetone that was flavored with candied orange peel and sliced almonds instead of the white bread. I also added the chopped chocolate to the warm cream while it was still simmering, then waited until it cooled a bit to add the yolks. I served it with a tbsp. of warmed store bought Fudge Grand Marnier sauce and a dollop of whipped cream. Incredibly decadent, but oh-so-good.

