Rating: 3
My husband is a bread pudding connoiseur and he loved this. It is particularly good eaten right after it has cooled down a bit, like warm chocolate pudding. It was incredibly easy and quick to make. However, I used stale croissants (about 2 large) and halved the butter. I also baked it in an oval shallow baking dish. We all agreed that it would be sinfully good with creme anglaise!